18/04/2003
OHRID, Macedonia -- A workshop aimed at improving the efficiency of prosecutors and court staff engaged in fighting human trafficking opened Thursday (17 April) in Ohrid. 
The event was organised by the OSCE Spillover Monitor Mission to Skopje and the US Justice Department's International Criminal Investigative Training and Assistance Programme. 
More than 40 prosecutors, investigative judges and police inspectors from Macedonia are attending. 
They will also discuss the legal changes needed to help authorities curb organised crime. 
(MIA - 17/04/03)
